  "text": "Gunay et al reported that NLR was positively correlated with CRP levels in COPD patients and found higher NLR values during acute COPD exacerbation compared with both stable COPD and healthy controls, 4.2, 2.0, and 1.7, respectively. [CITATION_1] In this study, hospitalized patients with noneosinophilic COPD exacerbations had two times higher NLR values than their eosinophilic counterparts. NLR was also correlated with CRP, and the Cox regression model showed that NLR (.7) was associated with a greater mortality rate in the 6 months follow-up.",
